django-admin startproject <project_name>
python manage.py runserver
python manage.py startapp <app_name>
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py shell
python manage.py shell_plus

python manage.py createsuperuser

pip install django_extensions









GIT INSTALL

Setup Git Configuration in Local
1. git config --global user.name "AerousZero"
2. git config --global user.email "srijanshakya77@gmail.com"
3. To verify; git config --global user.name
              git config --global user.email

Initialize A Repository In Local
1. git init  (But make sure you are in correct project location)

2. git status => Check the current status of the repo
3. git add . => Add all the changes to git repo
4. git commit -m "<commit-message>"
5. git push


git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/AerousZero/FirstDjangoProject.git
git push -u origin main

pip freeze > requirements.txt

pip install -r requirements.txt


POSTGRES DB
start a psql shell:
psql -u postgres (windows)

sudo -i -u postgres (linux)

for mac open shell 

CREATE DATABASE (name); (create a new DB)
